{"description":"If a class has the same name as a wrapper class : \r\n{code}\r\npackage foo;\r\nclass Character {}\r\n{code}\r\nThen if the bytecode of this class is not provided to the analyzer, this class will be (wrongly) resolved to java.lang.Character \r\n{code}\r\npackage foo;\r\nclass Foo {\r\nCharacter char \u003d new Character(); // \r\n}\r\n{code}\r\nThis can lead to an {{ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException}} as we assume that all constructors of java.lang.Character will have one argument. ","component":"SonarJava","component_version":"3.7"}